= Culture & Collaboration =

This section describes how we work together to build FactHarbor. We combine human values, structured decision-making, and automation to create a high-trust, high-impact environment.

== 1. Culture & Values ==

**[[Workplace Culture>>FactHarbor.Organisation.How-We-Work-Together.Workplace-Culture]]**
Our culture draws from three sources: the **[[Best Workplace Blueprint>>https://robertschaub.github.io/BestWorkplace]]** (human-centric), **Sociocracy 3.0** (structural), and an **AI-first philosophy** (technological).

**[[Continuous Improvement>>FactHarbor.Organisation.How-We-Work-Together.Continuous-Improvement]]**
How we use feedback loops, retrospectives, and metrics to ensure the system and the organisation are always getting better.

== 2. Structured Decision Making ==

**[[Consent-Based Decision Making>>FactHarbor.Organisation.How-We-Work-Together.Consent-Based-Decision-Making]]**
We use the Sociocracy 3.0 consent pattern for all system and policy changes. It ensures every concern is heard while maintaining high velocity.

**[[Global Rules>>FactHarbor.Organisation.How-We-Work-Together.GlobalRules.WebHome]]**
The shared standards that define how we evaluate evidence, handle risk, and maintain neutrality across the system.

== 3. Joining the Mission ==

**[[Contributor Processes>>FactHarbor.Organisation.How-We-Work-Together.Contributor Processes.WebHome]]**
Information for new and existing contributors on how to propose changes (RFCs), earn trust, and improve the system without manually editing content.

